09/07/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Police arrested four fellow officers Wednesday (July 8th), suspected of involvement in the trafficking of hundreds of women for prostitution.
A total of 25 people were arrested in the operation against what is considered one of the biggest women trafficking groups in Eastern Europe and the Balkans.
The group is believed to have trafficked almost 300 women to night clubs in Athens over the past several months.
In other news Wednesday, Iran released British-Greek journalist Iason Athanasiadis, a freelance reporter for the Washington Post.
Athanasiadis was arrested on June 23rd for illegal activities.
Iran also said his visa had expired.
(AP, Reuters, Immersia, BTA - 08/07/09)
